parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grinding noise when shifting from 1st to 2nd gear can indicate a serious transmission problem, potentially leading to premature wear, damage to gears and bearings, and even transmission failure, which can cause loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or crunching noise when shifting from 1st to 2nd gear
difficulty shifting
gears do not mesh correctly
skipping 2nd gear while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed muffler can lead to increased noise pollution, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially cause damage to other exhaust system components, which can lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: Loud exhaust noise
rattling or vibrating sounds from the exhaust system
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to retract
the seat belt becomes stuck
the seat belt is difficult to lock or unlock
the seat belt buckle remains locked and is hard to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the heating system to malfunction, leaving the driver and passengers without a functioning heating system, which can be a safety concern in cold weather conditions.
symptoms: No heat or little heat coming from the vents
coolant leaks
sweet or burning smell from the vents
fog or mist on the windshield
overheating engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ring Gear Slippage Behind Starter Teeth
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slippage of the ring gear behind the starter teeth can cause loud noises, difficulty starting the engine, and potentially lead to engine stalling or failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud grinding or screeching noises when starting the engine
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the brakes vibrate or pulse when applied
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.
